  "prompt": "Why are so many Quora users posting questions that are readily answered on Google?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why Quora users might post questions that could be answered through a simple Google search:\n\n1. **Desire for Personal Insights:** Users may be looking for personal experiences or nuanced perspectives that aren't easily found through a straightforward search. Quora allows users to get answers from people who may have firsthand knowledge or unique viewpoints.\n\n2. **Community Engagement:** Quora provides a sense of community and interaction. Users might prefer the engagement and discussion that comes from posting a question and receiving answers from real people.\n\n3. **Quality of Information:** While Google can provide a wealth of information, it can also yield a range of sources with varying reliability. Quora users might trust the answers provided by the community more than random search results.\n\n4. **Specific Expertise:** Users might be seeking answers from specific experts or people with particular expertise. Quora allows users to direct questions to certain individuals or topics, which can result in more specialized and informed responses.\n\n5. **Clarification and Context:** Sometimes, information found via Google can be overwhelming or confusing. Users might post questions on Quora to get clearer, more digestible explanations or to understand the context better.\n\n6. **Social Proof:** Seeing multiple responses from different users can provide a form of validation and consensus that a single Google result might not offer.\n\n7. **Convenience:** Some users might simply find it more convenient to ask a question on Quora rather than sifting through search results.\n\n8. **Follow-Up Questions:** Quora allows for follow-up questions and ongoing discussions, which can be helpful for users looking to explore a topic in depth.\n\nOverall, while Google is an excellent tool for finding information, Quora offers a more interactive and personalized experience that many users find valuable.",
